WEBVTT

00:06.506 --> 00:08.425
[opening theme music playing]

00:49.299 --> 00:51.968
STILL SHINING

01:06.399 --> 01:08.234
You two must have looked
inside the test room.

01:08.318 --> 01:09.444
Did it have a clock?

01:09.527 --> 01:10.445
It didn't.

01:11.237 --> 01:13.448
I'm sure they'll tell you the time,
but just in case,

01:13.531 --> 01:15.533
make sure you two bring watches.

01:15.617 --> 01:19.204
I'll pick you up at 7:00 a.m. tomorrow,
so come to the bus stop.

01:19.287 --> 01:21.247
-Don't be late.
-Okay.

01:23.124 --> 01:24.334
Go to bed early,

01:24.417 --> 01:26.961
make sure you eat breakfast,
and don't forget your packed lunch.

01:27.045 --> 01:29.464
And your exam ID slip. That's crucial.

01:29.547 --> 01:30.632
-Yes, sir.
-[Jeong-su] Okay.

01:31.674 --> 01:33.426
-Get a good night's sleep.
-[Eun-a] Okay.

01:37.096 --> 01:38.640
[cellphone ringing]

01:39.849 --> 01:40.850
[Jeong-su] Hello?

01:44.145 --> 01:46.564
Well, that…

01:46.648 --> 01:48.942
-[cellphone vibrates]
-You mean the paperwork?

01:49.734 --> 01:51.945
[Eun-a]<i> Let's meet at 6:50 a.m. tomorrow.</i>

01:52.028 --> 01:53.363
If you go in the room…

01:53.947 --> 01:55.198
The second drawer on the right.

01:55.281 --> 01:56.825
[Tae-seo] <i>Okay. Sleep tight.</i>

01:57.325 --> 01:58.743
[Jeong-su] It's there? I told you.

01:58.827 --> 02:01.037
Okay, I got it. [chuckles]

02:01.121 --> 02:03.123
Okay, bye.

02:10.338 --> 02:11.673
You didn't have to wait outside.

02:11.756 --> 02:13.800
-[Hwa-sun] Hello, Mr. Mu.
-[Jeong-su chuckling]

02:13.883 --> 02:15.760
You've gone above and beyond to help

02:15.844 --> 02:18.763
right up until the day before the exam.

02:18.847 --> 02:21.266
-We're really grateful.
-[Jeong-su] Not at all.

02:21.349 --> 02:24.018
It's my pleasure. [chuckles]

02:24.102 --> 02:28.231
Sir, Tae-seo needs a wristwatch,
but mine's digital.

02:28.314 --> 02:29.607
Do you have an analog one?

02:30.567 --> 02:33.027
This one's over 40 years old.

02:33.111 --> 02:34.487
It's fine as long as it works.

02:35.155 --> 02:36.781
-[chuckling]
-Is that so?

02:38.283 --> 02:39.617
Give me your hand.

02:40.243 --> 02:41.286
Put it on now,

02:41.369 --> 02:42.537
so you don't forget.

02:50.753 --> 02:53.214
[Jeong-su] You two did a great job
looking after him.

02:53.298 --> 02:56.009
-[Chang-sik chuckles softly]
-[Hwa-sun] You did far more for him.

02:56.092 --> 02:58.094
[gentle music playing]

03:47.769 --> 03:48.937
[Tae-seo] <i>Did you sleep well?</i>

03:49.020 --> 03:51.105
[Eun-a]
Yeah, better than I thought I would.

03:51.189 --> 03:52.982
I thought I'd be too nervous to sleep.

03:53.566 --> 03:57.237
I think knowing you'd be taking the exam
in the next room made me feel at ease.

04:00.782 --> 04:02.909
Did you wait long? You must've been cold.

04:03.576 --> 04:04.535
I'm hot.

04:04.619 --> 04:07.413
My dad said it's always cold in Korea
on exam day.

04:10.083 --> 04:11.084
I want to wear it.

04:20.677 --> 04:22.637
-Like this?
-[chuckling] No.

04:26.391 --> 04:29.310
Wrap it round and around,

04:30.728 --> 04:31.729
and then tie it.

04:37.819 --> 04:38.820
Mmm.

04:42.156 --> 04:45.410
My goal is to get into a school
as close to you as possible.

04:46.202 --> 04:48.913
If I can't get into one in Seoul,
then at least one nearby.

04:51.916 --> 04:55.086
Please let us both
achieve our goals today.

04:57.005 --> 04:58.006
I think

04:58.631 --> 05:00.300
this will help me do well.

05:01.467 --> 05:03.636
Give me something too. Anything of yours.

05:11.311 --> 05:13.855
Oh, I have something.

05:15.356 --> 05:16.357
[Eun-a gasps]

05:16.441 --> 05:18.568
YEONWOO HIGH SCHOOL
YEON TAE-SEO

05:19.152 --> 05:20.028
My lucky charm.

05:22.488 --> 05:26.034
EXAM ROOM 6

05:44.385 --> 05:49.640
STILL SHINING

05:49.724 --> 05:54.353
[Eun-a exclaiming joyfully]
The exam's over!

05:57.607 --> 05:58.608
Am I the only happy one?

06:02.612 --> 06:03.613
It's over!

06:04.614 --> 06:06.866
[Eun-a giggling] Wow.

06:06.949 --> 06:09.410
Tae-seo, let's go see the Hangang River.

06:09.494 --> 06:11.287
We've seen the ocean,
so we need to go there.

06:11.871 --> 06:13.039
But the time…

06:13.122 --> 06:14.248
Come on. We can make it.

06:15.625 --> 06:16.667
One second.

06:24.759 --> 06:25.802
I only have 7,000 won.

06:26.385 --> 06:27.386
Let's go next time.

06:31.682 --> 06:34.268
[Eun-a] I didn't use my allowance
since I was studying with you.

06:34.352 --> 06:36.604
You helped me save it,
so I should spend it with you.

06:36.687 --> 06:38.272
Come on, let's take the train.

06:46.155 --> 06:47.156
Not the train.

06:48.741 --> 06:49.742
Hmm?

06:58.042 --> 07:00.169
Let's see the river
from Dongseoul Bus Terminal.

07:00.253 --> 07:01.462
Can you see it from there?

07:01.546 --> 07:03.840
Yeah, the Hangang River is close
to Gangbyeon Station.

07:04.924 --> 07:07.218
We'll see the river,
leave from Gangbyeon Station,

07:07.301 --> 07:10.429
take the last train from Cheongnyangni,
and arrive early tomorrow morning.

07:10.513 --> 07:12.014
Why are we taking the train back?

07:12.598 --> 07:15.518
The train takes around six hours…

07:17.937 --> 07:21.357
so we can be together for longer.

07:22.525 --> 07:24.360
Oh, genius.

07:27.655 --> 07:29.699
What can we do with 7,000 won?

07:30.199 --> 07:32.827
Mmm… Buy me noodles from a tent bar.

07:32.910 --> 07:35.413
My dad said the noodles
in Seoul tent bars are really good.

07:36.581 --> 07:38.416
-Okay.
-[Eun-a chuckles]

07:39.625 --> 07:41.627
[pleasant music playing]

07:44.464 --> 07:45.465
Wow.

07:48.384 --> 07:50.636
-[Eun-a gasps] Want to go there?
-Okay.

07:52.430 --> 07:53.681
[woman] Here are your noodles.

07:53.764 --> 07:55.016
[in unison] Thank you.

07:55.099 --> 07:56.184
[Eun-a gasps]

07:58.478 --> 07:59.479
[both slurp]

08:01.272 --> 08:03.399
[Eun-a sighs in relief]

08:03.483 --> 08:04.942
It's familiar, but it's delicious.

08:06.360 --> 08:07.445
[Eun-a chuckles softly]

08:09.780 --> 08:11.741
I love noodles.

08:11.824 --> 08:15.453
And every time, my dad would say that
when my mom was pregnant with me,

08:15.536 --> 08:17.121
she'd always crave these noodles.

08:17.705 --> 08:19.832
I'd always wondered what they tasted like.

08:25.379 --> 08:26.547
I know.

08:26.631 --> 08:28.841
I'm always talking about my mom
when I come to Seoul.

08:28.925 --> 08:30.259
I don't miss her though.

08:32.261 --> 08:34.430
-[Eun-a slurps]
-Does she live here?

08:35.723 --> 08:36.849
No, she lives abroad.

08:37.683 --> 08:40.561
But I don't know where. I never asked.

08:42.230 --> 08:44.065
I'm sure she's doing well somewhere.

08:44.649 --> 08:47.693
Mmm. Somewhere that
has nothing to do with me.

08:52.532 --> 08:54.575
We can take the subway at 10:00 p.m.,
so don't rush.

08:55.618 --> 08:56.953
What about the Hangang River?

08:57.995 --> 08:59.580
You can see it from the station.

08:59.664 --> 09:00.957
Not from the station.

09:01.040 --> 09:02.833
I want to see it up close.

09:07.713 --> 09:08.631
We better eat quickly.

09:09.423 --> 09:11.425
[both slurping loudly]

09:14.136 --> 09:15.721
[Eun-a chuckles] Wow!

09:15.805 --> 09:17.848
The Hangang River's right in front of me.

09:17.932 --> 09:18.933
This is my first time.

09:19.016 --> 09:19.892
Me too.

09:19.976 --> 09:22.853
-[chuckles softly] Let's get a bit closer.
-Wait.

09:24.814 --> 09:25.856
You're…

09:26.607 --> 09:27.525
going to be cold.

09:29.402 --> 09:30.319
Wrap it round…

09:31.988 --> 09:32.989
and around,

09:33.573 --> 09:34.448
and then tie it.

09:34.532 --> 09:35.533
[Eun-a giggles]

09:37.785 --> 09:39.412
What about you? Aren't you cold?

09:39.912 --> 09:40.913
I can…

09:42.623 --> 09:43.666
just wear this.

09:54.468 --> 09:55.469
[Eun-a exclaims softly]

09:57.555 --> 09:58.556
It's a historic day.

09:58.639 --> 10:00.600
I saw both the ocean
and the Hangang River.

10:01.809 --> 10:03.436
I have to remember this day.

10:04.437 --> 10:06.355
[gentle music builds]

10:10.276 --> 10:11.277
Yeon Tae-seo.

10:11.360 --> 10:13.404
I just found my dream.

10:13.487 --> 10:14.488
Living on my own.

10:14.989 --> 10:16.407
Living away from my dad.

10:16.490 --> 10:18.868
This counts as a dream

10:18.951 --> 10:21.454
because it's only possible
if my dad gets better.

10:21.537 --> 10:23.998
If he's not doing well,
I can't even consider it.

10:24.081 --> 10:27.501
My dream is for my dad to get well
so I can become independent.

10:29.295 --> 10:30.296
How about you?

10:31.380 --> 10:32.381
Me?

10:33.132 --> 10:34.258
Mine is…

10:37.053 --> 10:39.430
If yours is independence,
mine is self-reliance.

10:40.014 --> 10:41.307
I don't have a "from."

10:42.642 --> 10:44.060
That's really amazing.

10:44.143 --> 10:45.561
[chuckles] What do you mean?

10:45.645 --> 10:48.898
[Eun-a] Because I know
you'll achieve that like it's nothing.

10:49.482 --> 10:52.318
From what I've seen,
you're good at doing things on your own.

10:53.819 --> 10:55.154
-I am?
-Yeah.

10:55.655 --> 10:57.573
I don't like doing things by myself,

10:57.657 --> 10:59.158
but you're really good at it.

10:59.241 --> 11:01.744
I've never seen you hang out with people.

11:02.244 --> 11:03.746
You're fine on your own.

11:04.246 --> 11:05.331
It's kind of amazing.

11:06.832 --> 11:07.833
Then again,

11:08.334 --> 11:10.461
I bet things will be different
when you go to college.

11:11.128 --> 11:14.632
[sighs] I wonder what else
will change about you.

11:16.509 --> 11:18.511
I doubt anything will change.

11:23.057 --> 11:24.058
Want to go a bit further?

11:25.726 --> 11:27.395
Yeah. Do we have time?

11:31.690 --> 11:33.484
No, we don't.

11:33.567 --> 11:34.610
[sighs sadly]

11:35.611 --> 11:36.612
Let's go.

11:37.530 --> 11:38.531
We have to go.

11:38.614 --> 11:39.824
Come on, we'll be late.

11:49.625 --> 11:51.919
[Eun-a laughing, panting]

11:52.002 --> 11:53.963
We walked way too far to see the river.

11:57.049 --> 11:58.175
Hold on.

11:59.218 --> 12:00.302
Gosh, I'm exhausted.

12:00.845 --> 12:02.096
I burned off all the noodles.

12:02.680 --> 12:05.266
[both laughing]

12:05.349 --> 12:06.851
[Tae-seo] Come on, we're late.

12:06.934 --> 12:09.603
[both panting]

12:09.687 --> 12:10.688
-[Eun-a gasps]
-Let's go.

12:10.771 --> 12:12.773
[romantic pop music builds]

12:16.861 --> 12:17.862
Run.

12:17.945 --> 12:19.947
[romantic pop music plays]

12:43.179 --> 12:44.221
[Eun-a] <i>This morning</i>

12:45.639 --> 12:46.765
<i>at the bus stop,</i>

12:47.266 --> 12:48.934
<i>I was watching you arrive.</i>

12:51.437 --> 12:53.439
[soft music playing]

13:07.036 --> 13:08.412
<i>Where we'll be,</i>

13:09.371 --> 13:10.372
<i>what we'll be doing,</i>

13:11.332 --> 13:12.333
<i>and with whom.</i>

13:13.918 --> 13:17.963
<i>I wondered which of these three</i>
<i>would be decided by today's exam.</i>

13:19.924 --> 13:20.925
<i>Then,</i>

13:21.634 --> 13:25.012
<i>could this be the last time</i>

13:25.513 --> 13:26.931
<i>we're headed</i>

13:28.557 --> 13:30.017
<i>in the same direction?</i>

13:33.354 --> 13:34.855
It's not certain yet,

13:35.898 --> 13:38.484
but things will change
when we're at different schools, right?

13:40.444 --> 13:41.445
No.

13:42.363 --> 13:45.866
Distance only mattered
when text messages didn't exist.

13:48.285 --> 13:50.246
If we can still send texts,

13:51.038 --> 13:52.414
no place is too far.

13:53.165 --> 13:54.708
We can text from anywhere.

13:54.792 --> 13:56.085
Exactly.

13:57.127 --> 13:58.712
Texting works everywhere.

13:59.213 --> 14:00.798
Even Yeonwoo has great service.

14:01.882 --> 14:05.761
Would texting not work somewhere
really remote in another country?

14:05.844 --> 14:07.721
Unless we're in different worlds,

14:09.014 --> 14:10.516
we can still text.

14:11.809 --> 14:13.143
[Eun-a] Different worlds…

14:15.187 --> 14:16.564
That's my mom and me.

14:19.817 --> 14:20.859
Same.

14:24.989 --> 14:27.366
There's something that only applies to us.

14:29.076 --> 14:30.536
Because it's you and me.

14:32.496 --> 14:37.543
You and I are going to try really hard
to spend time together.

14:39.295 --> 14:41.046
We'll make every effort.

14:43.173 --> 14:44.174
[chuckles softly]

14:45.676 --> 14:47.678
[Eun-a] You like me that much?

14:48.596 --> 14:49.597
Of course.

14:50.639 --> 14:52.641
If I hadn't been this sure,

14:54.685 --> 14:56.061
I wouldn't have even tried.

14:57.229 --> 14:58.397
Even when I had…

15:00.816 --> 15:03.569
no room in my life to like someone,
these feelings still grew.

15:24.548 --> 15:26.550
[music fades]

15:38.604 --> 15:40.606
[slow romantic music playing]

16:48.298 --> 16:49.758
I want to be with you.

16:54.555 --> 16:56.557
[music fades]

17:07.067 --> 17:08.736
[gate closes noisily]

17:12.239 --> 17:13.699
-Shall we?
-Yeah.

17:14.199 --> 17:15.159
Shall we?

17:18.620 --> 17:20.622
[crunching of footsteps]

18:05.125 --> 18:06.710
[Tae-seo whispering] Where should I go?

18:09.338 --> 18:10.339
Over there?

18:12.382 --> 18:13.383
[in English] Okay.

18:14.426 --> 18:16.428
[amusing music builds]

18:31.985 --> 18:33.987
[amusing music playing]

19:05.519 --> 19:06.520
[exhales]

19:22.828 --> 19:24.788
[in Korean] Your room is nice.

19:25.539 --> 19:26.540
Yeah.

19:44.016 --> 19:45.017
Let me…

19:45.601 --> 19:46.602
I can do it.

20:06.705 --> 20:08.707
[gentle music playing]

20:49.623 --> 20:50.624
[Tae-seo inhales]

20:52.167 --> 20:54.169
[sputters, coughs]

20:58.006 --> 20:59.007
Hold on.

21:33.959 --> 21:36.003
-[creaks]
-[Tae-seo] Sorry.

21:40.882 --> 21:42.926
[music continues playing]

22:21.298 --> 22:24.009
-[Seon-gyu] Eun-a, are you home?
-[music fades]

22:30.807 --> 22:33.101
-[whispers] Is that your dad?
-[knocking on door]

22:33.643 --> 22:34.728
[Seon-gyu] Eun-a.

22:34.811 --> 22:36.271
Yeah, Dad!

22:42.444 --> 22:43.612
I'm home.

22:45.030 --> 22:46.448
I'm going to wash up and go to bed.

22:46.531 --> 22:48.283
[Seon-gyu]
Are you going to school tomorrow?

22:48.366 --> 22:49.868
I have to, but I can go late.

22:50.786 --> 22:52.454
[stutters] Good night, Dad.

22:53.288 --> 22:54.748
Okay, well done today.

22:55.332 --> 22:56.333
Get some rest.

22:57.084 --> 22:58.418
I'm proud of you, my girl.

22:59.086 --> 23:00.087
Thanks.

23:00.921 --> 23:01.922
[chuckles softly]

23:05.133 --> 23:07.135
[receding footsteps]

23:08.637 --> 23:09.930
[sighs in relief]

23:16.019 --> 23:17.062
[whispers] Is he gone?

23:21.108 --> 23:22.109
[sighs in relief]

23:41.670 --> 23:42.671
[exhales]

23:46.174 --> 23:47.175
[Eun-a chuckles]

23:56.017 --> 23:57.018
No.

24:01.481 --> 24:03.817
Actually, I have a huge secret.

24:06.153 --> 24:08.780
I was too embarrassed to tell you.

24:23.378 --> 24:26.715
-[laughs]
-I was so hot I thought I'd die.

24:27.632 --> 24:30.218
I kept thinking about my thermals
as I took off my coat. [whines]

24:30.302 --> 24:32.512
It wasn't that cold today,
but my dad insisted.

24:32.596 --> 24:33.597
[shushes]

24:35.182 --> 24:36.683
This is so embarrassing.

24:36.766 --> 24:38.560
Why did it have to be floral?

24:41.771 --> 24:42.772
What?

24:43.899 --> 24:45.358
[whispers] I think it's cute.

24:52.824 --> 24:54.826
[gentle music playing]

24:56.578 --> 24:58.205
[Tae-seo chuckles]

25:30.654 --> 25:32.656
[indistinct chatter]

25:36.785 --> 25:38.870
[Jeong-su] You've always done well,

25:38.954 --> 25:40.497
so let's just figure out where to go.

25:40.580 --> 25:41.873
Go think about it.

25:41.957 --> 25:44.376
-Okay. Thank you.
-Off you go.

25:49.214 --> 25:50.340
My gosh.

25:57.931 --> 25:59.933
[soft music playing]

26:09.484 --> 26:11.987
[Jeong-su] Mo Eun-a, well done.
You did a good job.

26:12.737 --> 26:13.655
[Eun-a] Thank you.

26:14.489 --> 26:18.159
You did really well considering
you only started studying half a year ago.

26:19.035 --> 26:20.036
Really.

26:20.537 --> 26:22.163
If you'd started a year earlier,

26:22.998 --> 26:25.083
we could've tried
the regional admissions track.

26:25.583 --> 26:26.584
It's a shame.

26:27.168 --> 26:29.629
[inhales sharply, sighs] Now, let's see.

26:40.056 --> 26:42.058
[gate locks rustling]

27:06.124 --> 27:10.962
DECEMBER

27:11.046 --> 27:12.881
[music fades]

27:15.091 --> 27:17.552
[mouse clicking]

27:19.554 --> 27:21.431
DEPARTMENT OF MECHANICAL ENGINEERING

27:21.514 --> 27:23.016
YOUR APPLICATION HAS BEEN SUBMITTED

27:23.099 --> 27:24.309
All done.

27:24.392 --> 27:26.102
I'm so glad to have it submitted quickly.

27:27.270 --> 27:30.148
The results come out on February 4th, so…

27:30.231 --> 27:31.983
Just kick back and relax.

27:32.901 --> 27:34.277
Hmm.

27:37.489 --> 27:40.325
[So-hyeon exclaiming]

27:40.408 --> 27:44.788
[So-hyeon laughs] Yeah, it's beautiful.

27:46.206 --> 27:48.124
[So-hyeon chuckles]

28:03.515 --> 28:05.058
[whispers] Eun-a.

28:05.141 --> 28:07.018
-[thuds]
-[Eun-a exclaims softly]

28:08.019 --> 28:09.062
[Eun-a chuckles]

28:09.813 --> 28:11.981
Merry early Christmas.

28:13.900 --> 28:15.652
[laughs]

28:20.907 --> 28:24.035
[door slides open, closes]

28:25.745 --> 28:28.373
-The guests are here.
-Yeah, I'm all done.

28:28.957 --> 28:32.710
Oh, thanks to your help,
I'm officially on the concierge team now.

28:32.794 --> 28:34.671
-Thank you so much.
-[So-hyeon chuckles softly]

28:34.754 --> 28:37.507
I heard you specifically asked
to work with only me.

28:38.550 --> 28:40.760
Because you're good. [laughs]

28:43.304 --> 28:46.224
I think having to deal
with a different person each time

28:46.725 --> 28:48.560
bothers Seon-gyu a bit.

28:48.643 --> 28:50.186
He seemed to struggle with it.

28:51.229 --> 28:52.856
[smacks lips] So it's a win-win.

28:54.524 --> 28:56.860
Uh, you haven't had dinner yet, right?

28:56.943 --> 29:00.655
You eat this one,
and please take the other one to Eun-a.

29:01.823 --> 29:05.952
[sighs] Whenever the guests are here,
she never comes out of her room.

29:11.332 --> 29:13.209
[Eun-a] How did you feel
when you submitted it?

29:13.293 --> 29:16.796
Mr. Mu did it for me.
He clicked the "Submit" button too.

29:16.880 --> 29:18.047
He clicked it for you?

29:18.631 --> 29:20.508
I didn't ask him to,

29:20.592 --> 29:22.302
but it was just easier for him to do it.

29:23.845 --> 29:26.055
I'd be too nervous to click it myself.

29:28.433 --> 29:31.352
Do adults always have to deal
with stressful things like this?

29:31.936 --> 29:34.606
Why am I always so nervous and scared?

29:35.398 --> 29:37.484
[footsteps approaching]

29:37.567 --> 29:38.610
[light thud]

29:38.693 --> 29:39.944
[knock on door]

29:42.614 --> 29:43.615
[shushes softly]

29:56.753 --> 29:59.047
[humming]

30:05.094 --> 30:06.095
[chuckles]

30:09.015 --> 30:10.683
MY APPLICATIONS

30:10.767 --> 30:12.769
[quirky music plays]

30:15.104 --> 30:16.105
[Eun-a sighs]

30:18.691 --> 30:21.361
If you're done, I'll click it now.
I'm going to submit it.

30:21.444 --> 30:23.154
Mr. Mu, wait.

30:23.238 --> 30:26.199
-No, you've done more than enough.
-Please just wait.

30:26.282 --> 30:28.326
-I can't wait anymore.
-Wait, hold on!

30:28.409 --> 30:30.161
It's Christmas today.

30:30.245 --> 30:31.746
Can I just pray one time?

30:35.583 --> 30:36.960
I should get up to do it.

30:37.043 --> 30:39.045
-[chair thuds]
-It's okay. Just pray.

30:39.128 --> 30:41.631
-This gave me a bad feeling.
-Go on, just pray.

30:45.218 --> 30:47.303
Hopefully, we can make it home today.

30:49.764 --> 30:51.599
Dear Santa,
I really want to go to college.

30:51.683 --> 30:54.686
JANUARY

31:10.493 --> 31:11.953
[gasps] Oh, my god!

31:12.871 --> 31:14.372
Why are you hiding in the corner?

31:14.956 --> 31:15.957
It's so dark.

31:16.916 --> 31:18.585
-You should've turned the lights on.
-No…

31:20.253 --> 31:21.462
I'm fine.

31:27.385 --> 31:28.511
Please come over here.

31:54.162 --> 31:56.956
One thing's for sure.
We always have plenty to eat at our house.

31:58.166 --> 31:59.584
Enjoy your meal.

32:01.669 --> 32:03.796
We need the one you just swiped tonight,

32:05.340 --> 32:06.591
so take any of these instead.

32:08.509 --> 32:09.510
Okay.

32:10.094 --> 32:12.096
[quirky music playing]

32:42.377 --> 32:43.920
Happy New Year.

32:51.719 --> 32:52.720
[chuckles awkwardly]

33:07.902 --> 33:09.904
[music fades]

33:09.988 --> 33:11.990
[dog barking in distance]

33:29.173 --> 33:31.676
My first day as a 20-year-old
with Yeon Tae-seo.

33:36.931 --> 33:37.974
We don't have any glasses.

33:58.244 --> 33:59.245
It's sweet.

34:13.718 --> 34:14.969
It's pretty tasty.

34:15.511 --> 34:17.513
-[laughs]
-[slow pop music builds]

34:18.514 --> 34:19.640
It's not alcohol.

34:19.724 --> 34:21.184
It is alcohol.

34:27.190 --> 34:29.192
[slow pop music playing]

34:29.275 --> 34:30.359
[inhales sharply]

34:34.113 --> 34:35.114
[chuckles]

34:55.802 --> 34:57.095
Let's go.

35:01.516 --> 35:03.518
[both laughing, exclaiming gleefully]

35:19.283 --> 35:21.244
[both giggling]

35:29.544 --> 35:31.003
[yells] Eun-a!

35:31.546 --> 35:33.923
[laughing] Be quiet.

35:36.801 --> 35:38.469
[gasps, sighs]

35:42.598 --> 35:44.225
[both laughing]

35:44.308 --> 35:47.478
FEBRUARY

35:48.980 --> 35:51.607
[old man] All right, shall we toast?

35:51.691 --> 35:53.109
[all agreeing]

35:53.192 --> 35:54.986
Congratulations.

35:55.820 --> 35:59.115
He made it to Hanguk National University
from this tiny village. Congratulations.

35:59.740 --> 36:01.742
You're too kind. [chuckles]

36:01.826 --> 36:04.078
It's all thanks to Mr. Mu here.

36:04.162 --> 36:06.247
I didn't do much.

36:06.330 --> 36:08.166
He achieved it all on his own. [chuckles]

36:08.249 --> 36:10.418
[old man]
So did Mr. Mo's daughter not get in?

36:10.501 --> 36:11.961
[Jeong-su] No, she's still waiting.

36:12.044 --> 36:13.963
There's a first round of results,

36:14.046 --> 36:16.382
then a second, and even a third.

36:16.465 --> 36:18.259
The results come out in batches.

36:18.342 --> 36:20.386
So it's a little complicated. [chuckles]

36:20.469 --> 36:22.471
Gosh, you didn't have to.

36:22.555 --> 36:24.265
[Hwa-sun] Have some of this, Mr. Mu.

36:24.348 --> 36:25.600
-Congratulations.
-Great job.

36:25.683 --> 36:27.059
[Hwa-sun] Thank you.

36:27.143 --> 36:28.936
[old woman] So, Mr. Mu.

36:29.020 --> 36:31.355
Explain it properly so I can understand.

36:31.439 --> 36:34.400
Well, there is
an additional enrollment period,

36:34.483 --> 36:38.988
and the results don't finish coming out
until late February.

36:39.071 --> 36:40.948
What on earth does that mean?

36:41.032 --> 36:43.784
It must be killing Eun-a
to wait for the results.

36:43.868 --> 36:46.996
-[Jeong-su laughs] Right.
-[old woman sighs]

36:50.708 --> 36:52.376
[ocean waves crashing in distance]

36:52.460 --> 36:53.669
This is my first time.

36:54.462 --> 36:55.463
On the Sea Train?

36:56.714 --> 36:57.632
THIS IS THE SEA TRAIN

36:57.715 --> 37:01.385
[Tae-seo] It only runs during the day
and follows the coastline.

37:01.469 --> 37:04.472
It takes an hour and 40 minutes
from Gangneung to Samcheok,

37:04.555 --> 37:06.015
so if we go there and come back…

37:06.098 --> 37:08.893
We can be together
for around three and a half hours.

37:09.644 --> 37:10.645
Yeah.

37:12.855 --> 37:15.274
Uh, when I was little,

37:16.484 --> 37:18.778
my mom worked here for a bit.

37:20.029 --> 37:22.281
I wanted to become
a Sea Train driver back then.

37:23.407 --> 37:25.284
I guess it looked kind of cool.

37:25.368 --> 37:26.369
[chuckles softly]

37:28.371 --> 37:29.372
That's nice.

37:32.250 --> 37:34.418
What did you want to tell me
all the way out here?

37:41.467 --> 37:43.803
I have to go to Seoul soon.

37:45.429 --> 37:47.890
When I was living in Seoul,
I had a friend called Hyeong-seok.

37:47.974 --> 37:50.518
[inhales] And his dad runs a study center.

37:51.477 --> 37:54.730
He let me use it for free
and helped me out a lot.

37:56.023 --> 37:58.401
He asked if I could do some tutoring
starting in February.

37:59.235 --> 38:00.653
I'd been putting it off,

38:01.737 --> 38:04.365
but I think I really have to go now.

38:08.619 --> 38:09.620
[Eun-a] Right.

38:11.831 --> 38:12.832
You should go.

38:14.166 --> 38:17.003
And your entrance ceremony?
Is Hui-seo joining you later?

38:17.503 --> 38:19.005
He can't go. [inhales]

38:19.088 --> 38:20.840
He can't do long journeys yet.

38:21.424 --> 38:22.800
He must be upset.

38:24.051 --> 38:25.303
Do you have a place to stay?

38:25.386 --> 38:27.930
Yeah, the study center office has a bed.

38:28.014 --> 38:30.057
How can you sleep in an office?

38:30.641 --> 38:33.477
[sighs] That's so sad.

38:34.895 --> 38:35.896
That's nothing.

38:37.773 --> 38:40.026
You must be more sad
waiting for your results.

38:41.527 --> 38:43.696
[sighs] Me? Well…

38:44.238 --> 38:46.574
One of the three schools I applied to

38:46.657 --> 38:48.659
is at least close to you,

38:49.410 --> 38:50.953
but my chances of getting in are low.

38:51.537 --> 38:54.206
One is halfway between here and Seoul,
but it's not certain.

38:54.290 --> 38:56.751
The last one is in Gangneung.

38:57.877 --> 39:01.213
Mr. Mu said it's a good school,
and the program is good there.

39:02.089 --> 39:03.215
But…

39:04.300 --> 39:05.593
it's really far from you.

39:06.635 --> 39:10.890
Having to wait for over a month
is making me anxious and uncertain.

39:11.390 --> 39:13.309
It's been dragging on for so long

39:13.392 --> 39:15.311
that I can't believe
February is already ending.

39:15.895 --> 39:17.104
It feels endless.

39:26.530 --> 39:28.032
It's definitely going to end.

39:30.242 --> 39:31.952
I hope so.

39:35.956 --> 39:38.334
[gentle music playing]

39:40.336 --> 39:42.505
An end that really feels like one.

39:43.547 --> 39:45.758
I hope it's a clean end.

40:11.992 --> 40:12.993
Wait.

40:17.248 --> 40:19.417
This isn't much, but take it.

40:19.500 --> 40:21.001
I'm fine. I have money.

40:21.085 --> 40:22.795
Buy yourself something to wear.

40:24.380 --> 40:25.965
Your grandma seemed to feel bad

40:26.048 --> 40:28.717
we couldn't buy you something to wear

40:28.801 --> 40:31.053
to your entrance ceremony.

40:32.221 --> 40:34.348
We can't afford to buy you a suit,

40:34.432 --> 40:37.893
but at least buy yourself a coat.

40:37.977 --> 40:39.728
Something that's nice and formal.

40:40.479 --> 40:42.857
You'll need to dress up quite often
while in the city.

40:42.940 --> 40:45.067
Here. Buy one for yourself.

40:46.235 --> 40:47.236
Thank you.

40:49.822 --> 40:53.075
[Chang-sik] From scholarships to tutoring,
you're doing everything on your own.

40:53.159 --> 40:54.660
We feel terrible.

40:57.997 --> 40:58.998
I'll visit often.

41:00.124 --> 41:03.335
There's no need. You should be studying.
You'll only waste money.

41:04.587 --> 41:06.255
Just make sure you call Hui-seo.

41:09.216 --> 41:12.303
I thought he'd be grumpy
about missing your entrance ceremony,

41:12.803 --> 41:13.804
but he's been quiet.

41:16.807 --> 41:17.808
[inhales]

41:18.559 --> 41:22.521
At least the ceremony doesn't fall
on the same day as your parents' memorial.

41:23.731 --> 41:25.107
It's the first one.

41:26.609 --> 41:28.611
[melancholic music playing]

41:32.364 --> 41:34.408
I'll go pay my respects.

41:35.201 --> 41:36.619
Stay at home with Hui-seo.

41:41.749 --> 41:42.750
All right.

41:43.501 --> 41:44.502
Go on, then.

41:45.628 --> 41:46.629
Okay.

41:53.385 --> 41:58.057
WAITING AREA (TICKETS)

41:58.140 --> 41:59.183
[cellphone vibrates]

42:02.353 --> 42:05.439
[Eun-a]<i> Are you taking</i>
<i>the express bus to Seoul?</i>

42:06.482 --> 42:07.483
[Tae-seo] Eun-a.

42:11.612 --> 42:13.322
I was waiting right here.

42:13.405 --> 42:16.200
I thought you'd be taking the train.
I'm such a klutz.

42:17.910 --> 42:18.911
I just…

42:19.537 --> 42:22.456
I know you told me not to,
but I'd feel bad if I didn't see you off.

42:23.040 --> 42:25.584
I'll take you there.
I bought two tickets, so we can just go.

42:25.668 --> 42:26.919
Don't be ridiculous.

42:40.349 --> 42:42.685
How can you make me let you go home alone?

42:43.602 --> 42:44.853
You can let it happen today.

42:51.193 --> 42:52.695
Seriously, it's fine.

42:56.031 --> 42:57.533
Let's get off at the next stop.

42:58.367 --> 43:01.620
I can't bear to watch you go back alone.
I'll take you home and…

43:01.704 --> 43:03.247
So you can go alone, but I can't?

43:04.915 --> 43:06.750
That's nonsense. It's fine.

43:08.460 --> 43:09.878
[sighs]

43:09.962 --> 43:11.630
It's already been an hour.

43:11.714 --> 43:13.132
We don't have time.

43:13.215 --> 43:14.967
How long are you going to keep this up?

43:25.769 --> 43:28.063
LOG IN

43:31.108 --> 43:33.277
PLAYLIST

43:35.654 --> 43:36.655
This is my account.

43:37.448 --> 43:41.577
If I'm using it, it'll say,
"Currently streaming."

43:42.161 --> 43:44.580
We can use it together.
We'll listen to it at the same time.

43:45.331 --> 43:46.332
Then,

43:47.333 --> 43:49.251
it'll feel like we're together.

43:51.754 --> 43:54.882
-It'll feel like we're together.
-[Tae-seo] Feeling like we're together

43:56.258 --> 43:57.635
counts as being together.

43:58.177 --> 44:00.179
[gentle music playing]

44:01.263 --> 44:02.765
I like that. [chuckles softly]

44:02.848 --> 44:06.101
Hmm… What else is there
to make us feel together?

44:07.686 --> 44:10.564
Sharing the photos we take?
Let's take one now.

44:14.068 --> 44:15.069
Smile.

44:15.736 --> 44:16.737
[camera shutter clicks]

44:16.820 --> 44:18.030
[Eun-a giggles]

44:22.826 --> 44:25.162
Sir, how long will it take?

44:25.245 --> 44:26.163
[man] One hour.

44:26.246 --> 44:27.081
What?

44:29.750 --> 44:30.876
[Eun-a tuts]

44:30.959 --> 44:33.545
You should go. Let's part here.
It's your first lesson.

44:34.421 --> 44:35.422
Eun-a.

44:36.548 --> 44:37.716
[groans softly]

44:38.384 --> 44:40.135
This is a lot…

44:40.719 --> 44:42.262
harder than I expected.

44:43.138 --> 44:44.431
I can't do it.

44:45.182 --> 44:46.308
I can.

44:46.392 --> 44:49.436
Come on, I can't let you go back alone.

44:50.896 --> 44:52.523
You can. Just like this.

44:53.148 --> 44:56.735
I might end up at a college near you,
or I might not.

44:57.319 --> 44:58.862
I don't know what will happen.

45:00.781 --> 45:02.032
My life is always so uncertain.

45:03.659 --> 45:05.661
Anyway, we'll have to keep doing this,

45:05.744 --> 45:08.372
but if you feel bad or guilty,
it'll be hard to see each other.

45:11.375 --> 45:13.877
[sighs] This is driving me crazy.

45:16.839 --> 45:18.048
I'll…

45:18.632 --> 45:20.050
I'll do my best for us.

45:20.634 --> 45:21.635
[Eun-a] Okay.

45:21.718 --> 45:23.470
-[cellphone vibrates]
-Hmm?

45:28.642 --> 45:29.643
Oh, my god.

45:30.519 --> 45:31.562
What?

45:31.645 --> 45:33.355
What is it?

45:33.439 --> 45:34.481
I got in.

45:34.565 --> 45:35.732
What?

45:36.525 --> 45:38.235
GANGNEUNG WONKYEONG UNIVERSITY

45:38.318 --> 45:39.361
[exclaims]

45:39.445 --> 45:41.113
-No way! I got in!
-[exclaims, laughs]

45:42.072 --> 45:44.741
See? I got in because I was with you!
[exclaiming]

45:44.825 --> 45:47.035
Oh, my god. But it's a bit far from you.

45:47.119 --> 45:49.455
That's not what matters right now!

45:49.538 --> 45:50.539
[Eun-a shrieking]

45:50.622 --> 45:52.416
[Tae-seo] Congratulations!

45:52.499 --> 45:54.084
[lively music plays]

45:54.168 --> 45:57.588
-You really earned this.
-Oh, my god. I'm so happy.

45:57.671 --> 46:01.717
MARCH

46:03.844 --> 46:05.846
[music fades]

46:42.883 --> 46:43.884
[knocking on door]

46:45.010 --> 46:46.470
-[door opens]
-[man groans]

46:46.553 --> 46:49.264
-[woman exclaims] It's nice.
-[man] Nice and clean.

46:49.348 --> 46:53.060
-[woman] You must be his roommate.
-[man chuckles] I hope you two get along.

46:53.143 --> 46:56.104
-[girl] The bed here's so soft.
-[woman] Sweetie, don't sit there.

46:56.188 --> 46:58.482
[girl] Why not? Come try it too, Mom.

47:01.818 --> 47:02.986
[woman] This is nice.

47:15.624 --> 47:16.792
[Tae-seo] Hui-seo…

47:19.169 --> 47:21.088
I'll bring him over when he's a bit older.

47:24.424 --> 47:25.467
Mmm…

47:29.012 --> 47:30.806
Don't worry about him.

47:32.683 --> 47:34.560
[melancholic music playing]

47:34.643 --> 47:37.187
[voice shaking] And don't worry
about Grandma and Grandpa.

47:37.271 --> 47:38.480
[shudders]

47:41.984 --> 47:43.777
I'll take care of everyone.

47:47.739 --> 47:48.740
Mmm…

47:50.492 --> 47:51.702
[exclaims] I almost forgot.

47:53.829 --> 47:56.290
I'm attending the college
you wanted me to go to, Mom.

48:00.794 --> 48:01.795
[chuckles weakly]

48:03.589 --> 48:05.716
You would've been so happy
to see me there.

48:10.053 --> 48:11.054
[sniffles]

48:12.431 --> 48:14.641
[shudders] Mom.

48:17.311 --> 48:18.312
Dad.

48:20.188 --> 48:21.189
[sniffles]

48:34.745 --> 48:35.746
[sniffles]

48:46.673 --> 48:48.675
[sobbing]

48:58.935 --> 49:01.313
-[student] Can I sit here?
-[Eun-a] Sure.

49:12.449 --> 49:13.617
[student] I'm Park Na-ri.

49:14.451 --> 49:16.286
Oh, I'm Mo Eun-a.

49:18.121 --> 49:20.707
Hey, your student number
is right after mine.

49:21.291 --> 49:22.250
What a coincidence.

49:22.334 --> 49:24.169
[both chuckle]

49:24.252 --> 49:26.672
I'm from Seoul. You?

49:26.755 --> 49:28.757
I live nearby. Twenty minutes by bus.

49:28.840 --> 49:30.217
-[Na-ri] Twenty minutes?
-Yeah.

49:30.300 --> 49:32.302
[pleasant music playing]

49:36.306 --> 49:38.183
[Eun-a] No way!
We have the same elective too?

49:38.266 --> 49:40.602
No way! [chuckles] Come sit here.

49:47.734 --> 49:48.735
What's that?

49:52.698 --> 49:55.409
-[Na-ri] Want to pick one?
-[Eun-a] They're so cute.

49:55.492 --> 49:57.869
-Mmm… This one.
-Sure.

49:57.953 --> 49:59.830
-Here.
-Thanks.

50:00.914 --> 50:05.419
This class is called
Creative Engineering Design.

50:05.502 --> 50:07.295
This class will give you the opportunity

50:07.379 --> 50:10.882
to reflect on what lies
beyond the machines.

50:10.966 --> 50:12.926
Great machines are made
when you understand

50:13.009 --> 50:14.261
both their function and value.

50:14.344 --> 50:17.931
What you need for this class
is your mathematical ability

50:18.014 --> 50:19.683
and a brain that's capable of thinking.

50:19.766 --> 50:22.853
The rest you will learn
in this class today.

50:24.062 --> 50:26.231
Did you always want to study
early childhood education?

50:26.314 --> 50:28.233
Yeah, because I like kids.

50:30.026 --> 50:33.655
But teaching's not really for me.
It's not what I expected.

50:34.239 --> 50:35.323
[Na-ri sighs]

50:35.407 --> 50:38.577
I picked this place for the major,
but now, I'm not so sure.

50:40.662 --> 50:43.540
[sighs] But it's so nice to see the ocean.

50:44.750 --> 50:47.544
-This was worth skipping class.
-I know.

50:48.420 --> 50:51.798
Oh, I heard the vending machine coffee
was good here.

50:51.882 --> 50:54.134
SORI MARKET

50:54.217 --> 50:55.260
-Want to go?
-Let's go.

50:55.343 --> 50:57.387
[both laughing]

50:58.263 --> 51:01.391
[Eun-a] <i>We're already really close.</i>
<i>I'm exploring Gangneung thanks to her.</i>

51:01.475 --> 51:03.477
I'll take you around
the next time you're here.

51:03.560 --> 51:04.895
Okay.

51:07.272 --> 51:09.524
[Eun-a]
<i>I have matching stickers with Na-ri,</i>

51:09.608 --> 51:11.359
<i>but I don't have anything</i>
<i>matching with you.</i>

51:12.360 --> 51:13.361
Mmm…

51:14.488 --> 51:15.947
What do you want to do?

51:16.573 --> 51:19.159
Oh, I have a great idea.

51:19.242 --> 51:21.745
What if I make stickers with my drawings?

51:21.828 --> 51:24.289
<i>The same vegetable stickers</i>
<i>for our different classes.</i>

51:24.790 --> 51:25.832
<i>Tell me your classes.</i>

51:25.916 --> 51:27.417
I'll draw something for each one.

51:27.501 --> 51:29.544
-I'm really good.
<i>-</i>[Tae-seo] <i>Mmm…</i>

51:30.212 --> 51:31.463
Engineering Mathematics.

51:32.130 --> 51:33.131
[Eun-a] <i>Kidney beans.</i>

51:33.215 --> 51:34.800
It's extremely hard to pick them out.

51:34.883 --> 51:39.763
[chuckles] They're hard to pick out? Then…

51:39.846 --> 51:40.972
APRIL

51:43.475 --> 51:45.268
-[professor] Kim Na-rae.
-[Na-rae] Here.

51:47.062 --> 51:48.230
[professor] Kim Ji-ho.

51:49.648 --> 51:50.649
Ji-ho?

51:52.150 --> 51:54.027
-Mo Eun-a.
-Here.

51:55.487 --> 51:56.613
[professor] Park Na-ri.

51:57.405 --> 51:59.366
[student 1]
Right, Na-ri took a leave of absence.

52:00.367 --> 52:04.079
[student 2] It's only been a month,
and someone's already taking time off.

52:05.997 --> 52:08.041
-[professor] Park Seo-yeon.
-[Seo-yeon] Here.

52:08.124 --> 52:10.335
-[professor] Song A-yeong.
-[A-yeong] Here.

52:21.304 --> 52:22.472
PLAYLIST

52:29.271 --> 52:30.272
[camera shutter clicks]

52:31.523 --> 52:33.358
TAE-SEO

52:33.441 --> 52:35.402
[Eun-a]<i> Have the flowers</i>
<i>bloomed in Seoul yet?</i>

52:35.485 --> 52:37.153
<i>It's crazy here.</i>

52:37.237 --> 52:39.447
<i>Send me a photo of the flowers</i>
<i>at your school too.</i>

52:39.531 --> 52:43.118
<i>And a selfie of you in front of them too.</i>

52:47.080 --> 52:49.666
<i>I miss you, Tae-seo.</i>

52:50.750 --> 52:52.794
-[professor] Hello.
-[students] Hello.

53:01.428 --> 53:02.846
[chair thuds]

53:02.929 --> 53:04.848
-[cellphone vibrates]
-[gentle music playing]

53:05.682 --> 53:08.476
[Tae-seo]<i> I'll go to school after tutoring</i>
<i>and send it to you.</i>

53:23.158 --> 53:26.620
His tutoring session
usually takes about two hours, so…

53:28.330 --> 53:30.790
[Eun-a]<i> Call me</i>
<i>when you're done tutoring, okay?</i>

53:49.184 --> 53:50.894
<i>What time do you finish?</i>

53:51.770 --> 53:53.563
WHAT TIME DO YOU FINISH?

53:59.903 --> 54:01.237
[cellphone vibrates]

54:01.947 --> 54:03.740
[Tae-seo]
<i>I have two tutoring sessions today,</i>

54:03.823 --> 54:06.618
<i>so if I go straight to school after,</i>
<i>it should be around 10:00 p.m.</i>

54:16.628 --> 54:18.421
One ticket to Gangneung, please.

54:19.130 --> 54:20.340
[woman] Gangneung?

54:20.924 --> 54:22.217
That'll be 10,600 won.

54:26.888 --> 54:28.223
Dad.

54:29.599 --> 54:31.059
You never ask me to pick you up.

54:31.810 --> 54:32.894
I didn't want to go alone.

54:33.770 --> 54:35.647
[So-hyeon]
Are we going out for a night stroll?

54:35.730 --> 54:38.024
Where should we go? Let's go for sashimi.

54:39.943 --> 54:40.986
I'm tired.

54:55.542 --> 54:57.502
[So-hyeon sighs] What should we eat?

54:58.294 --> 54:59.796
Is there something you'd like to eat?

55:00.380 --> 55:01.923
I'm up for anything.

55:02.007 --> 55:04.175
[inhales sharply] Should we ask Eun-a?

55:04.259 --> 55:06.386
Eun-a, is there anything you want to eat?

55:07.512 --> 55:08.763
Eun-a, are you asleep?

55:10.306 --> 55:12.017
She must be really tired.

55:12.600 --> 55:13.601
Just let her sleep.

55:14.477 --> 55:16.479
[So-hyeon]
But we haven't gone out in forever.

55:16.563 --> 55:17.564
[cellphone vibrates]

55:17.647 --> 55:19.441
It'd be nice if we could talk while we go.

55:19.524 --> 55:21.401
[Tae-seo]
<i>I had no idea they'd bloomed so much.</i>

55:22.527 --> 55:23.611
<i>Should I call you?</i>

55:24.195 --> 55:25.447
<i>Is everything okay?</i>

55:25.530 --> 55:26.531
[camera shutter clicks]

55:26.614 --> 55:29.200
[Eun-a]<i> I was just wandering</i>
<i>and thought of you.</i>

55:29.284 --> 55:30.702
[camera shutter clicks]

55:30.785 --> 55:33.580
[Tae-seo]
<i>I can leave in the morning this weekend.</i>

55:33.663 --> 55:34.831
<i>Let's meet up early.</i>

55:35.749 --> 55:37.208
[Eun-a]<i> I want to go to Seoul.</i>

55:38.084 --> 55:39.252
[Tae-seo]<i> It's my turn to go.</i>

55:39.335 --> 55:40.628
<i>I'll come to you.</i>

55:40.712 --> 55:42.672
[Eun-a]<i> No, I'll go to you.</i>

55:42.756 --> 55:45.759
<i>Spend your time on yourself.</i>
<i>Don't waste it.</i>

55:45.842 --> 55:47.594
Hello, Hyeong-seok? Yeah.

55:48.136 --> 55:50.764
[Tae-seo] <i>Your time is precious too.</i>
<i>I'll go to you.</i>

55:52.182 --> 55:53.433
[camera shutter clicks]

55:55.477 --> 55:57.896
[Eun-a]
<i>My time right now is just passing by,</i>

55:58.688 --> 56:03.318
<i>but yours is time you need to use</i>
<i>toward your goals. They're different.</i>

56:05.487 --> 56:07.197
<i>No more dark photos.</i>

56:08.198 --> 56:10.116
<i>I miss you, Tae-seo.</i>

56:11.159 --> 56:12.160
<i>A lot.</i>

56:13.953 --> 56:15.955
[soft romantic music playing]

57:07.966 --> 57:08.967
[Tae-seo] This is nice.

57:09.050 --> 57:10.260
[Eun-a] Did you miss me?

57:12.137 --> 57:13.138
Of course.

57:16.391 --> 57:23.356
MAY

57:37.829 --> 57:41.374
[sighs] Every time I take out a cigarette,
you appear.

57:41.458 --> 57:43.376
It's almost scary. [chuckles wryly]

57:46.796 --> 57:48.590
It's fun working at a hotel, isn't it?

57:49.257 --> 57:51.134
I feel good
whenever I see the hotel staff.

57:51.217 --> 57:52.552
Then, try it out.

57:53.219 --> 57:55.638
A lot of local young people
work part-time at our hotel.

57:55.722 --> 57:56.973
Taking time off from school?

57:58.183 --> 57:59.809
What would I be taking time off for?

57:59.893 --> 58:01.686
I don't want to try things out
without a goal

58:01.769 --> 58:03.813
just because everyone else is.

58:04.731 --> 58:05.732
So annoying.

58:06.232 --> 58:09.861
[chuckles]
I mean, I know you're in college,

58:09.944 --> 58:12.322
but it's not even vacation time
and you're not at school.

58:12.405 --> 58:15.325
You've been here all day today
and riding your bike the past two days.

58:15.992 --> 58:17.202
You're the first one to ask.

58:17.785 --> 58:20.955
I skipped school all week and slacked off,
but no one's ever asked.

58:21.039 --> 58:24.542
No one from school reached out.
And my dad didn't ask why I wasn't going.

58:25.877 --> 58:27.462
I guess no one really cares.

58:28.046 --> 58:29.464
Thanks for asking.

58:29.547 --> 58:32.675
[tuts] I'm not going to school
because I don't feel like going.

58:32.759 --> 58:34.844
If you're going
to do college half-heartedly,

58:34.928 --> 58:37.180
you might as well take time off
and try something else.

58:37.263 --> 58:38.640
Don't you want to be independent?

58:39.265 --> 58:40.808
In your current situation,

58:40.892 --> 58:43.144
I doubt your dad would notice
you're not going to school.

58:43.228 --> 58:45.522
If I were you,
I'd be thinking about moving out.

58:47.982 --> 58:49.025
[scoffs]

58:49.108 --> 58:51.569
That came out of nowhere. What situation?

58:51.653 --> 58:53.488
Just go pick up your guests.

58:53.571 --> 58:56.866
It was a lunch reservation,
but it'll be dinner time soon.

58:57.909 --> 59:00.537
So-hyeon made
a surprise announcement today.

59:00.620 --> 59:02.622
I can't really ruin the mood.

59:03.122 --> 59:04.123
Announcement?

59:04.666 --> 59:05.583
[all laughing]

59:05.667 --> 59:08.294
-[man] You two look great together.
-[woman] I'm so happy for you.

59:08.378 --> 59:09.671
Congratulations.

59:09.754 --> 59:11.130
[all] Congratulations.

59:11.214 --> 59:12.131
Congratulations.

59:12.215 --> 59:14.217
-I'll bring out some more wine.
-All right.

59:16.928 --> 59:18.054
Cheers.

59:24.394 --> 59:26.396
Oh, you're here just in time.

59:26.479 --> 59:28.189
Your dad announced
they're getting married.

59:28.273 --> 59:29.649
You should congratulate them.

59:41.661 --> 59:43.663
[dramatic music playing]

59:51.379 --> 59:52.422
[grunts]

59:53.214 --> 59:55.008
[Eun-a] What about the Unit 610 guy?

59:55.091 --> 59:56.884
[So-hyeon] It took you long enough to ask.

59:57.427 --> 59:59.178
[breathes heavily]
I'll end things with him.

59:59.262 --> 01:00:00.763
[Eun-a] You're only ending it now?

01:00:01.806 --> 01:00:03.808
[So-hyeon] Seon-gyu knows everything.

01:00:04.601 --> 01:00:06.978
He said he'd tell me
once he figured things out,

01:00:07.061 --> 01:00:08.896
so I hadn't been able to end things.

01:00:10.898 --> 01:00:11.899
Eun-a.

01:00:11.983 --> 01:00:16.654
Love doesn't happen in perfect order.

01:00:16.738 --> 01:00:18.656
No wonder why
you always have a guy around.

01:00:18.740 --> 01:00:20.241
There's never a break with you.

01:00:20.325 --> 01:00:22.201
-Watch what you say.
-You watch it.

01:00:22.285 --> 01:00:23.953
How dare you two-time my dad?

01:00:24.912 --> 01:00:25.955
[sighs]

01:00:27.123 --> 01:00:30.001
[smacks lips] Seon-gyu is the one
I have feelings for.

01:00:30.084 --> 01:00:31.628
The one in Unit 610 knows that too.

01:00:31.711 --> 01:00:34.172
I've never deceived or misled anyone.

01:00:34.255 --> 01:00:36.716
So you're saying
you'll live however you want

01:00:36.799 --> 01:00:38.718
and everyone else
has to just deal with it?

01:00:39.886 --> 01:00:42.055
And my dad just accepted that nonsense?

01:00:44.682 --> 01:00:46.225
What do you take my dad for?

01:00:47.101 --> 01:00:49.395
He's a good person,
but someone like you…

01:00:49.479 --> 01:00:50.813
[So-hyeon] This is the last time.

01:00:50.897 --> 01:00:52.815
I'll let your insults slide today,

01:00:52.899 --> 01:00:54.233
but after this,

01:00:54.859 --> 01:00:56.110
not a chance.

01:01:01.282 --> 01:01:02.283
[Seong-chan] Mo Eun-a.

01:01:05.036 --> 01:01:06.287
Mo Eun-a!

01:01:07.038 --> 01:01:08.039
Let go.

01:01:08.790 --> 01:01:10.249
You should congratulate them.

01:01:10.333 --> 01:01:12.085
You're startling our guests.

01:01:12.168 --> 01:01:13.628
Take this and go back inside.

01:01:13.711 --> 01:01:15.630
[sarcastically]
You're so damn good at your job.

01:01:19.759 --> 01:01:23.137
Aren't you a little old to be so worked up
over your dad's relationship?

01:01:24.180 --> 01:01:25.556
You should focus on your own life.

01:01:27.558 --> 01:01:28.851
I'll try to find you a job.

01:01:31.562 --> 01:01:32.980
I can't promise it'll help though.

01:02:08.307 --> 01:02:09.308
[chuckles]

01:02:09.809 --> 01:02:12.145
[gentle music playing]

01:02:18.568 --> 01:02:19.694
[chuckling]

01:02:30.913 --> 01:02:33.541
[professor] It tends to stop or flip over
on steep inclines.

01:02:34.292 --> 01:02:36.252
[student 1]
Could the weight distribution be off?

01:02:36.335 --> 01:02:38.379
[student 2]
How about switching to two-wheel design?

01:02:38.463 --> 01:02:41.174
-[Eun-a]<i> Are you busy?</i>
-[Tae-seo]<i> I'm in my professor's lab.</i>

01:02:41.257 --> 01:02:42.925
<i>It's only for grad students,</i>

01:02:43.009 --> 01:02:45.511
<i>but the TA let me in,</i>
<i>so it's my first time here.</i>

01:02:45.595 --> 01:02:46.554
<i>It's pretty cool.</i>

01:02:47.096 --> 01:02:49.807
[Eun-a] <i>You sound busy.</i>
<i>What time do you finish?</i>

01:02:49.891 --> 01:02:53.603
[Tae-seo]<i> What is it?</i>
<i>If it's urgent, I can call you right now.</i>

01:02:53.686 --> 01:02:56.773
-You should be majoring in flattery.
-[all laughing]

01:02:56.856 --> 01:02:59.150
Honestly. We'll continue this in a bit.

01:02:59.233 --> 01:03:01.694
-[Eun-a]<i> Never mind. I'll catch you later.</i>
-[student 1] Yes.

01:03:02.403 --> 01:03:04.906
The professor likes supreme pizza.

01:03:04.989 --> 01:03:07.200
-Could I go use the restroom?
-Yeah, sure.

01:03:07.950 --> 01:03:09.827
-Professor, please have some.
-[professor] Mmm.

01:03:10.620 --> 01:03:11.621
[cellphone vibrates]

01:03:13.915 --> 01:03:15.124
[Eun-a]<i> Did you know?</i>

01:03:15.875 --> 01:03:18.878
<i>Apparently, you can see Namsan</i>
<i>from anywhere in Seoul.</i>

01:03:19.504 --> 01:03:22.340
<i>So from now on, your name is Namsan.</i>

01:03:22.924 --> 01:03:23.925
<i>Yeon Namsan.</i>

01:03:26.636 --> 01:03:30.056
<i>I guess I'm still stuck in uncertainty.</i>

01:03:31.140 --> 01:03:33.142
[exhilarating music playing]

01:03:38.523 --> 01:03:39.607
[Tae-seo]<i> Where are you?</i>

01:03:40.525 --> 01:03:41.609
[Eun-a] <i>The wetlands.</i>

01:03:42.151 --> 01:03:45.279
<i>No. I'm actually at the bus stop now.</i>

01:03:48.950 --> 01:03:50.451
[cellphone vibrating]

01:03:50.535 --> 01:03:51.786
TAE-SEO

01:03:57.917 --> 01:03:59.252
[Tae-seo] <i>You're in Seoul, right?</i>

01:04:00.795 --> 01:04:03.714
[Eun-a] <i>While I was wandering,</i>
<i>I was going to buy some makeup</i>

01:04:03.798 --> 01:04:05.466
<i>and get a bowl of noodles.</i>

01:04:06.133 --> 01:04:09.303
<i>You have important things going on.</i>
<i>Don't waste your time.</i>

01:04:09.387 --> 01:04:10.805
<i>I have plenty of time,</i>

01:04:11.806 --> 01:04:12.807
<i>so I'll drop by again.</i>

01:04:13.516 --> 01:04:15.184
[Tae-seo]<i> Don't be ridiculous.</i>

01:04:15.268 --> 01:04:17.311
<i>Nothing matters more</i>
<i>than us being together.</i>

01:04:24.026 --> 01:04:27.655
[Eun-a] <i>Tae-seo, I really want to see you.</i>

01:04:33.077 --> 01:04:34.120
[sighs]

01:04:34.203 --> 01:04:35.246
[Tae-seo]<i> I'm on my way.</i>

01:04:35.955 --> 01:04:37.540
[Eun-a] <i>You don't know where I am.</i>

01:04:38.624 --> 01:04:39.625
[Tae-seo] <i>Hang on.</i>

01:04:40.751 --> 01:04:42.753
[music fades]

01:04:44.088 --> 01:04:46.674
[slow pop music playing]

01:04:46.757 --> 01:04:47.717
[digital beeps]

01:04:47.800 --> 01:04:49.886
[Tae-seo] <i>I have one more stop.</i>
<i>I'm almost there.</i>

01:05:01.856 --> 01:05:03.316
GANGBYEON STATION

01:05:11.991 --> 01:05:13.451
[train horns honks]

01:05:13.534 --> 01:05:16.829
[Eun-a]<i> I can hear Yeon Tae-seo coming.</i>

01:05:27.298 --> 01:05:29.342
<i>I'm done wandering.</i>

01:05:32.303 --> 01:05:35.222
STILL SHINING

01:06:01.040 --> 01:06:04.085
[man] <i>You were really going through it</i>
<i>before you did your military duty.</i>

01:06:04.794 --> 01:06:06.337
[Tae-seo] <i>I hate goodbyes.</i>

01:06:07.254 --> 01:06:08.756
For 10 years, I'd forgotten.

01:06:09.966 --> 01:06:11.300
<i>They were gone.</i>

01:06:11.384 --> 01:06:13.094
Eun-a…

01:06:13.177 --> 01:06:15.054
You haven't heard from her, have you?

01:06:15.763 --> 01:06:16.973
<i>Let's stop…</i>

01:06:18.265 --> 01:06:20.101
<i>with the worries and everything else.</i>

01:06:20.184 --> 01:06:21.352
[Eun-a] <i>I thought of you.</i>

01:06:24.563 --> 01:06:27.274
<i>I had hoped to see you at least once.</i>

01:06:34.323 --> 01:06:36.325
Subtitle translation by: Hyesoo Lee
